<title>JAPAN: TABLE - Japan May c/a surplus jumps 154.9 pct.</title>
<headline>TABLE - Japan May c/a surplus jumps 154.9 pct.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-07-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>The surplus in Japan's current account, the broadest measure of trade in goods and services, rose 154.9 percent to 906.8 billion yen in May from a year earlier, the Ministry of Finance (MOF) announced on Wednesday.</p>
<p>The surplus in merchandise trade alone rose 118.6 percent from the same month a year earlier to 927.9 billion yen, the ministry said.</p>
<p>The following is a breakdown of the balance of payments figures:</p>
<p>(Unadjusted, in bln yen)	MAY	 APRIL    YEAR AGO</p>
<p>Current Acct Balance	 +906.8    +1,091.8	+355.7</p>
<p> -Goods and Services	 +412.8	+417.6	-104.1</p>
<p>    Trade Balance	    +927.9    +1,022.6	+424.5</p>
<p>	 Exports		3,984.9     4,313.4     3,314.8</p>
<p>	 Imports		3,057.0     3,290.8     2,890.3</p>
<p>    Services Balance	 -515.1	-604.9	-528.7</p>
<p> -Income Balance	     +575.2	+744.8	+538.0</p>
<p> -Current Transfers	   -81.2	 -70.7	 -78.2</p>
<p>The following figures show the unadjusted balance in Japan's capital and financial accounts (in billions of yen):</p>
<p>				   MAY	    APRIL     YEAR AGO</p>
<p>Capital/Financial Acct   -830.7	   -860.5	-479.1</p>
<p>-Financial Account	 -817.1	   -819.2	-487.9</p>
<p> Direct Investment	 -223.2	   -313.8	-143.6</p>
<p> Portfolio Investment    +148.9	   +111.2	-427.6</p>
<p> Other Investment	  -732.8	   -616.6	 +83.3</p>
<p> Capital Account	    -13.6	    -41.3	  +8.9</p>
<p>The following figures show the adjusted balance of payments figures (in billions of yen)</p>
<p>				 MAY	   APRIL</p>
<p>Current Account Balance  +1,272.8    +1,015.9</p>
<p> -Goods and Services	 +813.0	+518.9</p>
<p>    Trade Balance	  +1,380.7    +1,015.4</p>
<p>	 Exports		4,480.8     4,319.3</p>
<p>	 Imports		3,100.1     3,303.9</p>
<p>    Services Balance	 -567.7	-496.5</p>
<p> -Income Balance	     +558.7	+600.0</p>
<p> -Current Transfers	   -98.8	-103.1</p>
